    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="755"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d755">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/11902a.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to all
                            <gloss type="to">American diplomatic missions</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Circular telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 11, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Plans for mediation are progressing satisfactorily. General Huerta has appointed
                    representatives to attend the conference, which will begin May 18, at Niagara
                    Falls, Canada. The President has appointed as representatives Associate Justice
                    Lamar of the Supreme Court and Honorable Frederick Lehman, former Solicitor of
                    the Department of Justice. Hostilities are suspended between General Huerta and
                    the United States, but continue between General Huerta and the
                    Constitutionalists, also between General Huerta and Zapata, who controls a
                    section of Southern Mexico. The question of Carranza’s participation in the
                    conference not yet determined.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
